The paper deals with communication over a fading channel with unknown sparse impulse response, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked communications (cs.NI). The proposed receiver scheme involves belief propagation, which is a popular technique in statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of bit-interleaved coded orthogonal frequency division multiplexing (OFDM), which is a common technique in digital signal processing (cs.LG).
